cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Congestion Control Experiment Results with QUIC under Varying Scheduler
  and Slow-Path Conditions
abstract: This dataset captures network performance evaluations of QUIC-based congestion
  control algorithms under emulated latency and bandwidth constraints. Experiments
  vary scheduler policies and slow-path network profiles across client-server-proxy
  topologies, measuring throughput, latency, and energy consumption. Archive contents
  include environment setup scripts, topology configuration files, per-run logs with
  synchronized metrics, and structured result directories. Evaluation focuses on adaptive
  scheduling behavior and protocol performance under controlled network emulation
  scenarios.
